editorialNotes.short: Learn to read and pronounce words with your new friend!
editorialNotes.tagline: Learn to read with a friend

editorialNotes.standard: Learning the ABCs is child's play with this entertaining and educational app. Adorable artwork, colorful creatures, and smooth voice and sound effects enhance an already engaging hands-on experience that makes spelling each and every word an interactive puzzle.

Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivated—and Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new ‘dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

editorialNotes.short: Try a wild new look – risk-free!

editorialNotes.tagline: Build your own gears and engines

ios.subtitle: Create to show what you know!
Audio to help relax and sleep
Take your friends for a swim

name: Sight Words Ninja - Slicing Game to Learn to Read

editorialNotes.short: See internal organs in action: lungs breathe, muscles bend and nerves respond to a pinprick.

ios.subtitle: The fun way to learn to write

editorialNotes.standard: The line never ends at Dr. Panda’s Ice Cream Truck, and that’s just how our kids like it. They jump at the chance to whip up new flavors and serve sky-high sundaes piled with toppings. Watching customers gobble down their desserts cracks them up every time (and us too).

editorialNotes.short: Create unique animal species and test their mobility.

editorialNotes.standard: Kids (and kids at heart) can unleash their inner scientists with this captivatingly clever robot-creation kit, which features millions of different combinations for mechanical inventions. Whether you’re assembling a wheeled bot with laser guns for arms or a jolly jumping automaton with pogo-stick legs, taking your new bot on a walk through the woods will highlight the success—or the rough edges—of your design. While The Robot Factory teaches some nifty physics basics, we like to play around just for the pure fun of it.
editorialNotes.short: Design and experiment with all types of robots.

editorialNotes.standard: We’ve played so many games that we feel like we could create our own—and now we can, all without coding classes or complex tutorials. With this ingenious educational app, it's easy to become a designer. Imagination rules as you build characters, worlds, and stories for one-of-a-kind games meant to be saved, shared, and—of course—played.

Slide a shape into the correct hole—easy, right? It is, at first. But what makes Busy Shapes so clever is the way it gently gets more challenging, motivating little kids to find solutions to each puzzle through experimentation. From shape-changing to color-mixing to hidden holes, we’re impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.

Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way that’s delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.

ios.subtitle: Be a vet and heal the animals

editorialNotes.standard: Fox and Sheep’s endearing app gives kids the power to heal—and helps parents encourage kindness and curiosity. Through trial and error, little ones figure out how to treat a sniffly owl, a sunburned rabbit, and other beautifully animated patients. Sometimes they need bandages and medicine; sometimes a healthy snack will do the trick. Animals’ flashbacks and reactions offer important clues in the delightful quest to make them smile again.

In this imaginative animated storybook, two of Sesame Street’s most popular characters team up to spark your child’s love of reading. As fearful Grover concocts hilarious obstacles to keep kids from reaching the last page, eager Elmo asks for their help to discover the mysterious monster at the end of the story. It’s an engaging experience that teaches bravery and conflict resolution through lively interactivity, adorable artwork, and heartwarming humor. Parental tips help you integrate these lessons during storytime and beyond, combining learning and play with practical advice from a name you can trust.

editorialNotes.tagline: Play with sun, wind, and air
editorialNotes.standard: Once again, the creators of The Human Body and Simple Machines have turned playtime into a rich learning experience. Tinybop’s sandbox-style app lets kids experiment to their hearts’ content—seeing what happens when they move the sun, whip up winds, and cause rainstorms. A zoomed-out view illustrates the broader water cycle at work, while fascinating closeups show things like the effects of changing temperatures and strengthening tornadoes on everyday life. We also dig the detailed study guide offering extra info and discussion ideas.

ios.subtitle: Fun math practice in a maze!
Truck racing games for kids HD

editorialNotes.standard: If you can think it, you can build it with this app for kids. Assemble voice disguisers, kaleidoscopes, alarms, and more with plenty of guidance that will get makers of all ages up and running.
editorialNotes.short: Teach kids to invent and program with this powerful maker app.
